      "description": "Photographic and performative reinterpretation of Abaporu (1928), by Tarsila do Amaral. Through self-representation, contemporary photography and post-conceptual strategies, the work operates as a critical reflection on the circulation of images, the updating of visual repertoires, and the mechanisms of cultural appropriation and intertextual dialogue.",
